# Database Conventions

## Model Naming
- Use PascalCase for model names (e.g., `Game`, `GameFrame`)
- Use snake_case for field names (e.g., `created_at`, `player_order`)
- Prefix related model names with parent model (e.g., `GameFrame`, `GameScore`)

## ID Fields
- Use UUID as primary keys
- Field name: `id`
- Type: `String` with `@id @default(uuid())`

## Relationships
- Use singular form for model names
- Foreign key format: `model_id` in snake_case
- Always define explicit relations using `@relation`
- Use unique constraints for composite keys

## Timestamps
- Use `created_at` for creation timestamp
- Use `ended_at` (optional) for completion timestamp
- Type: `DateTime`